        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build and cook",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{vegetable-oil}} in a pan over medium heat. Fry the {{onion}} for 5 minutes. Add the {{garlic}}, {{ginger-root}}, {{cumin-ground}}, {{coriander-ground}}, {{turmeric}}, {{chilli-powder}}, and {{tomato-puree}} and cook for 1 minute. Transfer to the slow cooker. Add the {{chickpeas-tinned}}, {{tinned-tomatoes}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Cook on low for 6 hours. Stir in the {{garam-masala}} and {{spinach}} (if using) at the end, the spinach wilts in 2 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Reduce to 5 hours for next time. Slightly broken chickpeas thicken the sauce, not a bad result if the texture is otherwise good",
              "cause": "Six hours is long for tinned chickpeas",
              "symptom": "Chickpeas very soft and beginning to collapse"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add a pinch of caster sugar and taste. An extra tablespoon of tomato puree also helps round a sharp sauce",
              "cause": "High-acid tinned tomatoes",
              "symptom": "Sauce thin and sharp"
            },
            {
              "fix": "The blooming step on the hob is essential. Without it the spices taste raw rather than warm and rounded",
              "cause": "Spices not bloomed before slow cooking",
              "symptom": "Curry tastes flat"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chickpea curry is the simplest vegan slow-cooker dinner in this collection. The ingredients are all from the pantry, nothing fresh needed beyond onion, garlic, and ginger. It keeps well in the fridge for three days and improves with each reheating. Serve with basmati rice and flatbread.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
